---
/**
 * City record — Tower 01: Porter, the local strategy agent.
 * Facts from github.com/MattisEngelhardt/Porter-Local-Strategy-Agent.
 */
import Record from '../../layouts/Record.astro';

const title = 'Porter — A Fully Local AI Strategy Agent | Mattis Engelhardt';
const description =
  'Porter is a local AI research and strategy agent by Mattis Engelhardt: research tasks go in, professional PDF briefs, PowerPoint decks and Excel models come out — 100% on-device, no cloud, no API costs.';
---

<Record
  title={title}
  description={description}
  tower="Tower 01"
  name="Porter"
  lede="A research department that fits on one laptop — and sends no data anywhere."
  accent="sun"
  github="https://github.com/MattisEngelhardt/Porter-Local-Strategy-Agent"
  next={{ href: '/city/amadeus', label: 'Tower 02 — Amadeus' }}
>
  <section class="act">
    <h2>The brief</h2>
    <p>
      Porter turns research-heavy questions into boardroom-ready
      deliverables: PDF briefs, PowerPoint decks, formula-driven Excel
      models, Markdown briefings. The unusual part is where it runs —
      entirely on the machine in front of you. Local language models,
      local search, local memory. No API key, no cloud bill, no data
      leaving the room.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="act">
    <h2>How it runs</h2>
    <p>
      One task moves through a six-phase pipeline, and a single effort
      dial (<em>low / high / ultra</em>) decides how hard the machine
      thinks — how many research workers run in parallel, how many
      rounds they take, whether a critique pass revises the output
      before it ships.
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>Intent parsing — the task is understood, effort auto-detected</li>
      <li>Clarification — one to three rounds of targeted questions</li>
      <li>Multi-agent research — parallel workers fetch and rank findings via SearXNG</li>
      <li>Synthesis — findings consolidate into structured analysis</li>
      <li>Output generation — briefs, decks and workbooks render</li>
      <li>Critique &amp; revision — the work gets reviewed before it leaves</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="act">
    <h2>Details that matter</h2>
    <p>
      Porter remembers. Every analysis is embedded into a local vector
      store — run it on the same company twice and it opens with what
      changed since last time. Voice input is one shortcut away,
      transcribed on-device. And in document mode it reads internal
      PDFs and spreadsheets without touching the web, with every figure
      in the synthesis traced back to its source — built for the
      CEO-office use case where hallucination is not a quirk but a
      dealbreaker.
    </p>
    <p class="aside">
      Design stance: fail open. A missing dependency prints its exact
      fix and the other deliverables still ship. Scaling effort, swapping
      models or backends is configuration, never code.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="act">
    <h2>Stack</h2>
    <p class="stack mono-label">
      Python &middot; Ollama / LM Studio &middot; SearXNG &middot;
      ChromaDB &middot; WeasyPrint &middot; python-pptx &middot;
      openpyxl &middot; faster-whisper
    </p>
  </section>
</Record>
